<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-28T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/864: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-28T09:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                        1919, 9 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department’s August 20, 6 p.m. Commander Gayler left 25th for Washington
                            via Cuba and Key West with protocol, article 3, section 2 of which
                            should read, after “Haiti” as of December 31, 1916 as acknowledged by
                            the Haitian Government on the 12th of April 1919”.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>